cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it proposes a mechanism to maintain fairness in a peer to peer network. It may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it mentions the implementation of the mechanism in a distributed system. Additionally, it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a ranking mechanism for peers based on their resource contributions. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with the interactions between peers in a network. Finally, it may belong to the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category as it proposes a mechanism that converges faster than existing approaches.
